    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Hezekiah no doubt believed that in the \"counsel\" of Eliakim and Isaiah, and in the \"strength\" promised him by Egypt, he had resources which justified him in provoking a war.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Vain words - literally, as in margin, i. e., a mere word, to which the facts do not correspond. ",
        "children": [
